式，您之间传输文件的设备之间的距离必须在 16 英尺以内。设备可见性设置可帮助防止垃圾邮件和不需要的文件传输。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/googles-nearby-share-app-for-windows-pcs-is-now-officially-available-180032189.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/googles-nearby-share-app-for-windows-pcs-is-now-officially-available-180032189.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7d646ef3-e373-43a5-9da5-e98575dbcf6b</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 19 Jul 2023 18:00:32 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689788801</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T17:46:44+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="676" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/d0527100-265a-11ee-bd6f-dfe9c7a6dfde" width="1200"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="676" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/d0527100-265a-11ee-bd6f-dfe9c7a6dfde" width="1200"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Google]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Google Nearby Share graphic]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Google Nearby Share graphic]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Apple is reportedly developing its own generative AI chatbot to rival ChatGPT]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在这场方兴未艾的“人工智能战争”中，苹果公司一直保持着令人怀疑的沉默，直到现在。 <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-07-19/apple-preps-ajax-generative-ai-apple-gpt-to-rival-openai-and-google?sref=10lNAhZ9">据<em>彭博社最初报道，该公司正在创建自己的聊天机器人。</em></a>工程师们厚颜无耻地将工具集命名为“AppleGPT”，但它实际上被称为 Ajax，因为大型语言模型 (LLM) 是使用 Google 的 JAX 框架构建的。消息人士称，苹果有多个团队致力于该项目，其中一个团队致力于解决潜在的隐私问题。</p><p>苹果实际上会用这个机器人做什么？目前尚不清楚，因为该公司似乎没有关于用例场景、发布日期或平台的任何可靠计划。一位不愿透露姓名的消息人士告诉<em>彭博社</em>，预计明年将发布正式公告以及更多细节。苹果公司下个月还将举行年度财报电话会议，这可能会对 Ajax 的情况产生一些影响。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>在此之前，苹果首席执行官蒂姆·库克向<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.goodmorningamerica.com/News/video/tim-cook-apple-vision-pro-change-people-engage-99863168"><em>《早安美国》</em></a>表示，公司正在“密切关注”生成式人工智能。据<em>彭博社报道</em>，John Giannandrea 和苹果软件工程高级副总裁 Craig Federighi 正在领导该计划。 Giannandrea 最初受聘来监督 Siri 及其机器学习功能，所以也许这个陷入困境的数字助理将会变得更加有用。</p><p>近几个月来，生成式人工智能领域呈爆炸式增长，几乎所有大型科技公司都加入了炒作行列。就在昨天， <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-and-microsoft-release-llama-2-an-ai-language-model-for-commercial-use-163615807.html">Meta 和微软发布了 Llama 2，</a>这是一款用于商业用途的人工智能聊天机器人。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/apple-is-reportedly-developing-its-own-generative-ai-chatbot-to-rival-chatgpt-174507671.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apple-is-reportedly-developing-its-own-generative-ai-chatbot-to-rival-chatgpt-174507671.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ba2d437c-e938-40d8-bb85-8765cd7df656</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 19 Jul 2023 17:45:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689788757</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T17:46:00+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="3781" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/80d842c0-265b-11ee-9ab8-ccd20ac66b4e" width="5672"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3781" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/80d842c0-265b-11ee-9ab8-ccd20ac66b4e" width="5672"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - An Apple logo adorns the facade of the downtown Brooklyn Apple store on March 14, 2020, in New York. Apple became the first publicly traded company to close a trading day with a $3 trillion market value, marking another milestone for a technology juggernaut that has reshaped society with a line-up of products that churn out eye-popping profits. (AP Photo/Kathy Willens, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Apple $3 Trillion]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Instagram beats copyright infringement lawsuit involving embedded photos]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://gizmodo.com/instagram-wins-copyright-claims-case-on-embedded-photos-1850651894"><ins>据</ins><em><ins>Gizmodo 报道，美国第九巡回上诉法院的三名法官组成的陪审团做出了有利于 Meta 旗下 Instagram 的裁决，此前两名摄影师指控这家社交媒体巨头侵犯版权。</ins></em></a>该案的基本要点是，Instagram 在未经内容创作者明确同意的情况下允许外部网站和出版物嵌入图像，从而侵犯了版权。</p><p>该案可以追溯到2016年，当时<em>《时代》</em>杂志在未经许可的情况下嵌入了摄影师马修·布劳尔(Matthew Brauer)拍摄的希拉里·克林顿(Hillary Clinton)的Instagram照片。 2020 年， <em>Buzzfeed</em>对亚历克西斯·亨利 (Alexis Hunley) 拍摄的“黑人生命也是命”抗议活动的照片做了同样的事情。这对照片起诉 Instagram，声称该社交媒体公司从未要求第三方获得嵌入受版权保护的照片或视频的许可，从而导致他们面临二次侵权指控。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该诉讼最初于 2021 年在加利福尼亚州提起，但法官驳回了诉讼，理由是相关新闻媒体没有存储原始图像，甚至没有显示其副本。相反，它只是将 Instagram 上已有的内容显示为嵌入内容。两人对这一决定提出上诉，但现已在联邦法院失败。其推理<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Scribd;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=cc8a75f0-b695-4a6a-a33c-41019f4bfaa4&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Scribd&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAY-0x8M71cUg3wGZPv38IvH_ntW1D1PBqknCl5tPNUFI&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F659785820%2FHunley-Brauer-Instagram-Appeal" class="rapid-with-clickid"><ins>与加州的判决相同，</ins></a>法官们一致认为，嵌入照片或视频时，不会复制底层内容。</p><p>然而，值得注意的是，联邦法官小组确实表示，亨利和布劳尔对版权所有者实际控制并最终从其作品中获利的能力提出了“严重且经过充分论证”的政策担忧。 Instagram 也在几年前解决了这个问题，并在 2021 年添加了一个选项，允许用户将图像设置为不可嵌入。这一变化是在该平台受到美国媒体摄影师协会 (ASMP) 和国家新闻摄影师协会 (NPPA) 游说后做出的。</p><p>这件事可能还没有结束，据<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.reuters.com/legal/transactional/column-instagram-dodges-photographers-copyright-claims-appeal-case-likely-2023-07-18/"><em><ins>路透社</ins></em><ins>报道</ins></a>，摄影师可以请求与 11 名随机选出的法官组成的小组进行重新听证，尽管布劳尔和亨利尚未讨论这一行动方案。</p><p>这也是法院判决的潜在含义。该裁决本身表明，媒体出版物等第三方可以随意嵌入照片和视频，而无需征求原始内容创建者的许可。然而，相关案件不断涌现，但结果却各不相同，为更高一级法院的摊牌埋下了伏笔。</p><p>例如，一名纽约法官在 2018 年做出了一项<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/business/business-news/judge-rules-news-publishers-violated-copyright-by-embedding-tweets-tom-brady-photo-1085342/"><ins>有些矛盾的裁决</ins></a>，当时一名摄影师在各种出版物中嵌入了 NFL 传奇人物汤姆·布雷迪 (Tom Brady) 的原始图像的推文后起诉了这些出版物。法官站在摄影师这边，在她的判决中指出，“该图像托管在由无关第三方拥有和运营的服务器上这一事实并不能保护他们免受这一结果”，并补充说“版权法没有任何地方表明为了显示图像，必须拥有图像。事实上，该法案的目的和语言支持相反的观点。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/instagram-beats-copyright-infringement-lawsuit-involving-embedded-photos-170547770.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/instagram-beats-copyright-infringement-lawsuit-involving-embedded-photos-170547770.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 2577faf4-65f1-4d18-8b31-cd579abe6dab</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 19 Jul 2023 17:05:47 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689786349</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T17:05:59+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="3210" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5e70e440-2650-11ee-9f3d-eca4e21bccd1" width="4918"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3210" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/5e70e440-2650-11ee-9f3d-eca4e21bccd1" width="4918"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Anadolu Agency via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ANKARA, TURKIYE - JUNE 26: In this photo illustration the logo of âInstagramâ  is displayed on a mobile phone screen in Ankara, Turkiye on June 26, 2023. (Photo by Didem Mente/Anadolu Agency via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Instagram]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best grills and grill accessories in 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>野餐季节到了，所以现在是时候确保您拥有终极烧烤设置所需的一切了。为了帮助您准备花更多的时间在户外，我们整理了一份最好的烤架和烧烤配件清单，供您在门廊、甲板、露台或后院进行烹饪冒险。我们审查和测试了各种烤架和其他设备，并选择了我们的首选来帮助您在烧烤游戏中保持领先。还有其他户外烹饪物品，其中的选择可以帮助您成为烧烤大师，全年提供美味的食物并在此过程中扩展您的技能。</p><h2> <strong>Traeger Timberline 和 Timberline XL</strong> </h2><p><core-commerce id="0a0c5dc436aa45ec92cab2a220b50f7a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>去年，Traeger <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/traeger-timberline-2022-smart-grills-announced-price-specs-163043089.html">全力</a>打造智能烧烤炉。该公司完全重新设计了其高端<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy50cmFlZ2VyLmNvbS9wZWxsZXQtZ3JpbGxzL3RpbWJlcmxpbmUiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3MGUzZjBmLWQ1NzMtMzViNC1iYWY3LTY3MTE4ZDQ3YTVmZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAY6xk7AJryYndkbXlUQosd_ev4NmjvSQodyPfMedOgBX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.traeger.com%2Fpellet-grills%2Ftimberline">Timberline 系列</a>，将其优质颗粒烤架转变为户外厨房。虽然烹饪室可能看起来与任何其他 Traeger 烤架一样，但该公司决定将这些新型号放在滚动推车上，而不是四条腿上。当然，这可以为您提供更多存储空间，但也可以更轻松地清空颗粒料斗。烤架的正面和侧面有一个导轨系统，可容纳一系列配件，从纸卷到酱汁、钳子和摩擦隔间。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>在技​​术方面，Traeger 更换了之前配备 WiFi 的 D2 烤炉的基本控制装置，转而采用彩色触摸屏。内部有更多传感器来密切关注烹饪过程，并添加照明以帮助您在天黑后更好地看到烹饪表面。新的 Timberlines 还将与专门设计的无线 Meater 探头配合使用（Traeger 于 2021 年购买了 Meater），因此您不必依赖标配的有线版本。也许最重要的是，该公司添加了据称是首款用于酱汁、配菜和烧烤的户外感应燃烧器。</p><p>所有这些升级的起价为 3,500 美元。如果你可以放弃其中一些细节（例如，我认为你的烤架不需要触摸屏），那么自从我<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-04-24-traeger-ironwood-650-review-wifi-pellet-grill-smoker.html">在 2019 年</a>评测第一代 Ironwood 以来，它一直是我的主力。它仍然运行得像冠军一样，并且与该公司的全功能应用程序配合得很好。对于想要深入研究颗粒烤架的人来说，这是一个不错的选择，它比 Traeger 的入门级 Pro 系列提供更多功能。尽管该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/traegers-redesigned-ironwood-grills-pack-touchscreen-controls-and-more-efficiency-150010372.html">在 2023 年更新了型号</a>，但仍然销售原版 Ironwood，并且您可以比最小的新 Timberlines 便宜 2,000 美元购买更大尺寸的产品。</p><h2>韦伯创世纪 II EPX-335 </h2><p><core-commerce id="739991f14ecd487b9b008a144071da88" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> 2021 年，Weber 推出了<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/weber-connect-smart-gas-grills-171237945.html">首款智能燃气烧烤炉</a>。在为<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/weber-smokefire-review-wifi-pellet-grill-140000499.html">SmokeFire 颗粒烤架</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-04-03-weber-connect-smart-grilling-hub-review.html">智能烧烤中心</a>开发 Weber Connect 平台后，该公司将其 Wi-Fi 连接烹饪引入了更广泛使用的燃料来源。 <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/weber-2022-grill-lineup-genesis-smokefire-weber-connect-140518150.html">去年</a>，该公司对 PureBlu 高热燃烧器、烧烤区、边桌、可扩展顶部烹饪炉排和“夜视”LED 照明进行了一些改进。如果 2022 <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Weber USA;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=de57025b-1082-4622-af33-0312dca51a60&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Weber+USA&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiJkZTU3MDI1Yi0xMDgyLTQ2MjItYWYzMy0wMzEyZGNhNTFhNjAiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud2ViZXIuY29tL1VTL2VuL2dhcy9nZW5lc2lzLzM3ODEwMDAxLmh0bWwiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3MGUzZjBmLWQ1NzMtMzViNC1iYWY3LTY3MTE4ZDQ3YTVmZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAWNp3XItqsMdY7aDMg6z_PvLs2xhizIR1RSh294cx8u0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weber.com%2FUS%2Fen%2Fgas%2Fgenesis%2F37810001.html">EPX-335</a>不能满足您的需求，还有其他选择，包括带有搪瓷或不锈钢饰面的三燃烧器和四燃烧器配置。另外，还有丙烷和天然气型号，如果您需要，有些型号还配有侧燃烧器。</p><p>当然，这里的主要吸引力是 Weber Connect 集成。就像在 SmokeFire 颗粒烤架和智能烧烤中心上所做的那样，该技术可以指导您完成烧烤过程的每一步。 Weber Connect 应用程序内的说明和视频组合为各种技能水平的烧烤者提供帮助，甚至包括何时翻转牛排。更重要的是，该系统可以在您的手机上提供实时食物温度和估计的准备倒计时，以便您可以更好地安排蔬菜串等配菜的时间（并阻止饥饿的人群）。在其燃气智能烤架上，Weber Connect 还可以密切关注燃油油位，以便您知道何时需要更换油箱。</p><p>韦伯还推出了一系列烧烤工具套件和配件，以扩展其燃气烧烤炉的功能。该公司生产烧烤手套、烤架、烤篮、烤肉架和披萨石，以及刮刀和刷子等烧烤清洁工具。还有一个煎锅插件，可以让您制作从早餐到粉碎汉堡的所有食物。如果您想改造整个烧烤区域，Weber 有一个全尺寸的煎锅配件可以做到这一点。</p><h2>奥尼披萨烤箱</h2><p><core-commerce id="a1df6d80b4494684a121634dae76d6ca" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Ooni Pizza Ovens;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0de15002-ec35-49d8-b24c-3d060213cd2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Ooni+Pizza+Ovens&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZGUxNTAwMi1lYzM1LTQ5ZDgtYjI0Yy0zZDA2MDIxM2NkMmIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9vb25pLmNvbS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3MGUzZjBmLWQ1NzMtMzViNC1iYWY3LTY3MTE4ZDQ3YTVmZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAejJfnRtktOMij-Jitrj0piUQHMLO_lU1a5e1lGHJHw5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fooni.com%2F">Ooni</a>因其披萨烤箱而享有盛誉，这是理所当然的。该公司的设备易于使用，可帮助您在家中制作餐厅品质的木烤馅饼。其最新的烤箱<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Ooni Pizza Ovens;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0de15002-ec35-49d8-b24c-3d060213cd2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Ooni+Pizza+Ovens&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZGUxNTAwMi1lYzM1LTQ5ZDgtYjI0Yy0zZDA2MDIxM2NkMmIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9vb25pLmNvbS9wcm9kdWN0cy9vb25pLXZvbHQiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3MGUzZjBmLWQ1NzMtMzViNC1iYWY3LTY3MTE4ZDQ3YTVmZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAc7iXMdDoNMe27-IgSMEKvH98algnZ6Mz2591oR0mscX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fooni.com%2Fproducts%2Fooni-volt">Volt 12</a>是<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/oonis-volt-12-is-the-companys-first-indoor-pizza-oven-173011466.html">一款电动型号</a>，可在室内使用，但仍然具有我们逐渐信赖的 Ooni 功能。就纯户外烤箱而言， <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Ooni Pizza Ovens;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0de15002-ec35-49d8-b24c-3d060213cd2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Ooni+Pizza+Ovens&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZGUxNTAwMi1lYzM1LTQ5ZDgtYjI0Yy0zZDA2MDIxM2NkMmIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9vb25pLmNvbS9wcm9kdWN0cy9vb25pLWthcnUtMTYiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3MGUzZjBmLWQ1NzMtMzViNC1iYWY3LTY3MTE4ZDQ3YTVmZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZ2X4F3mbN9UOqUErPIldeXLDV-t5um34Yjod-1N-VY9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fooni.com%2Fproducts%2Fooni-karu-16">Karu 16</a>可以容纳多种燃料源，并有空间容纳更大的披萨。该型号开箱即可燃烧木材或木炭，但 Ooni 的<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Ooni Pizza Ovens;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=0de15002-ec35-49d8-b24c-3d060213cd2b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Ooni+Pizza+Ovens&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiIwZGUxNTAwMi1lYzM1LTQ5ZDgtYjI0Yy0zZDA2MDIxM2NkMmIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9vb25pLmNvbS9jb2xsZWN0aW9ucy9nYXMtYWRhcHRvcnMiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3MGUzZjBmLWQ1NzMtMzViNC1iYWY3LTY3MTE4ZDQ3YTVmZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAZsNWK3AZH-x6EftxJ7_yJZ1FrpzmW98jeDxLwF15C0P&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fooni.com%2Fcollections%2Fgas-adaptors">燃气燃烧器</a>售价为 120 美元和 150 美元（丙烷和天然气版本）。</p><p>除了整体尺寸外，Karu 16 还具有一些与 Ooni 的其他烤箱不同的便利性。首先，铰链门可以让您通过玻璃窗看到正在烹饪的食物。其次，有一个前置数字温度计，可以显示烤箱内部的环境温度。与其他 Ooni 披萨炉一样，Karu 16 加热速度很快，大约 15 分钟内即可达到 950 华氏度。当然，更大的烹饪区将允许您制作披萨以外的东西。如果您可以忍受较小的烤箱和模拟温度计，该公司最近推出了 Karu 12G，它仍然具有玻璃门，提高了燃油效率，并且可以配备燃气燃烧器附加装置（100 美元）。</p><h2> Thermoworks Thermapen 一号</h2><p><core-commerce id="67c57640f62d4f9facef1bbb4981e360" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>多年来，Thermapen 已成为我最常用的烧烤工具。我像副主厨一样依靠它来确保我烹饪的食物达到正确的内部温度，尤其是鸡肉。它是烧烤和厨房中的多功能且坚固的工具。 ThermoWorks 的<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:ThermoWorks;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=8ec42127-5c25-4160-a755-9edb36e27b1b&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=ThermoWorks&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4ZWM0MjEyNy01YzI1LTQxNjAtYTc1NS05ZWRiMzZlMjdiMWIiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlcm1vd29ya3MuY29tL3RoZXJtYXBlbi1vbmUvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI3NzBlM2YwZi1kNTczLTM1YjQtYmFmNy02NzExOGQ0N2E1ZmQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAaga3aSO_DiG9sWk_mFdWFcwY2u1QIwaLZ0DkYjYOJ85&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thermoworks.com%2Fthermapen-one%2F">Thermapen One</a>是其最畅销的 Thermapen Mk4 的后续产品。这款新型号显示温度快如闪电，一秒钟即可读数。 ThermoWorks 还提高了准确性，并使用了比以前的型号更亮的显示屏。自动旋转屏幕使数字无论您如何握住都可以轻松查看，此外，自动唤醒和睡眠功能可延长电池寿命，IP67 防护等级可防止意外泼溅。</p><h2><strong>肉加</strong></h2><p><core-commerce id="11305a24fae04a50999ec3df162997c1" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>当有这么多很棒的（而且价格实惠）的有线选项可用时，无线肉类温度计似乎有点大材小用。一开始我也持怀疑态度，但我可以向你保证，当你翻转或包裹一大块肉时不必避开那些金属电缆绝对值得投资。对于<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9NRUFURVItVGhlcm1vbWV0ZXItUm90aXNzZXJpZS1CbHVldG9vdGgtQ29ubmVjdGl2aXR5L2RwL0IwN0g4V1RGSFc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tdTItMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6Ijc3MGUzZjBmLWQ1NzMtMzViNC1iYWY3LTY3MTE4ZDQ3YTVmZCJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAXPGqap9KATMqeh2AGAOSNcZNlKoeM7OekPdkYZxVk-_&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMEATER-Thermometer-Rotisserie-Bluetooth-Connectivity%2Fdp%2FB07H8WTFHW%3F">Meater Plus</a> ，这家 Traeger 旗下公司扩展了原始型号的蓝牙范围。每个探头都有两个传感器，因此您可以密切关注烤架的内部食物温度和环境温度。统计数据会发送到公司的应用程序，您可以设置目标温度、查看预计完成时间或在需要时获得烹饪方面的帮助。</p><h2> Anova 精密炊具 Nano 3.0 </h2><p><core-commerce id="15ab066d1aea4c88b52c6bafedda7456" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Anova Precision Cooker Nano 的最新版本仍然以紧凑的外形提供真空低温烹调功能。这是我长期以来一直使用的畅销书的更新版本，这主要归功于它的准确性和可靠性。该公司已将蓝牙连接更换为双频 WiFi，因此您可以远离<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Anova Culinary;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=ce1fdbb0-87c7-4856-a25a-d4bfd4a8b910&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Anova+Culinary&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWzLclrAZYzNouP6ntRP4NYvHiclp57i37i_sKBU-DJk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fanovaculinary.com%2Fproducts%2Fanova-precision-cooker-nano-3">Nano 3.0</a>进行更远的冒险。该型号还具有两行触摸屏显示屏，因此可以同时查看时间和温度。如果您想绕过 iOS 或 Android 应用程序，这里也存在手动控制。该软件将为您提供食谱和分步指导，因此即使您对这种烹饪方法有经验，也最好查阅它。</p><p>为了充分利用您的真空低温烹调设备，您还需要购买真空密封机。我有<a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQS2Rwktsr_B9EeOTE4eXtVxzj6xvX38m7BfdRPHCpd9&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFoodSaver-FM2000-Machine-Starter-Certified%2Fdp%2FB01D5TMBE0">FoodSaver FM2000</a> 。它没有更昂贵的设备的一些华而不实的功能，但它涵盖了基本功能。如果您喜欢更坚固的产品，例如自动袋子检测、可伸缩手持式密封机和干/湿设置等选项，我会推荐<a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATAoqpg-fCggIU0Hr5acSnJASH3lOLTM712H28jFwzOX&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FFoodSaver-V4440-Automatic-Detection-Certified%2Fdp%2FB00DI342B4">FoodSaver V4400</a> 。有了这两种产品，除了真空低温烹调之外​​，您还可以用它们来密封冰箱里的剩菜，或者储存您不希望空气接触到的其他物品。我还发现真空密封包装可以方便地重新加热手撕猪肉之类的东西。当您用真空低温烹调法重新加热时，肉不会像在微波炉中那样变干。当然，您可以只使用密封袋，但我已经这样做了，并且 FoodSaver 值得投资。</p><h2> Stanley IceFlow 玻璃杯</h2><p><core-commerce id="5879d3ab06a24492bee0a7f70676855e" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>我认为最重要的烧烤工具之一是冷饮。随着天气越来越热，您需要仔细计划您的饮料用具，以便您的怪物鸡尾酒或供水保持在寒冷的温度。多年来我尝试过多种隔热铝杯，但 Stanley 是最好的。该公司以其经典的保温瓶而闻名，但其杯子、瓶子等系列产品价格实惠，并且可以一次将饮料保冷数小时。</p><p> Stanley 有很多选择可以替代 Yeti 等流行品牌，但<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Stanley;elmt:;cpos:20;pos:1;pdid:IceFlow Tumblers" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=997aab74-1490-44a1-a718-9a438f559b4c&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Stanley&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfuZ8IyegUzsh5PJkbrBOxbnmMkgiYLGe4a-d5uMg3AS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stanley1913.com%2Fproducts%2Fthe-iceflow-flip-straw-tumbler-30-oz" data-demonetize-referrer="https://fave.co/2TgQcqC" class="rapid-with-clickid">IceFlow 玻璃杯</a>是我今年春天的首选。较大的 30 盎司杯子可以将饮料冷藏长达 12 小时，而 20 盎司版本则可以冷藏长达 7 小时。有一个坚固的手柄和内置的翻转吸管意味着饮用区不会太多地暴露在自然环境中。这些产品的价格分别为 25 美元和 30 美元，只是最昂贵产品成本的一小部分，而且它们的冰保留能力也比其中一些产品更好。</p><h2> <strong>Brumate Hopsulator 二重奏和三重奏</strong></h2><p><core-commerce id="9e68d4dc662f45a0a8b6e4097ff729d9" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Brumate 的 Hopsulator 产品对我来说是温暖天气的必需品。我最初买的是海滩用的，但它已成为我烧烤工具箱中的必备品。该公司的<a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAWET3NaWN0QnQF8ikHsCJcCjERczE-MZtiAHrvJEarao&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBr%25C3%25BCMate-HOPSULATOR-Stainless-Insulated-Glitter%2Fdp%2FB07FW8C54H%3Fth%3D1">Hopsulator Trio</a>是一款 3 合 1 选项，可容纳 16 盎司罐头或 12 盎司罐头，并带有可放在冰箱中的冷插入件。它还配有盖子，因此您可以将其用作旅行杯。 <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAckpEf3IL6jqzHPiR8iBQ_YjcpxEZsl-UqTnM3ilWMAh&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBr%25C3%25BCMate-Hopsulator-DUO-2-Stainless%2Fdp%2FB08NC3LP15%3F">Hopsulator Duo</a>还可以兼作保温杯，但它专为 12 盎司罐装设计，不配备任何冷却配件。此外，Brumate 还推出了第三种<a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAcuaRR6I5wGcUddjfI4A_yowkj6OHLpkkJO4SrTq5mWB&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBr%25C3%25BCMate-HS12T-Hopsulator-Slim-Aqua%2Fdp%2FB07K2JW273%3F">细长罐</a>型号。因此，如果您更喜欢硬苏打水，那么您也可以选择。</p><p></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/best-grilling-gear-143011296.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-grilling-gear-143011296.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 770e3f0f-d573-35b4-baf7-67118d47a5fd</guid><dc:creator>比利·斯蒂尔</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:30:08 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689784209</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T16:30:25+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[weberconnectsmartgrillinghub]]></category><category><![CDATA[anova]]></category><category><![CDATA[ironwood650]]></category><category><![CDATA[thebuyersguide]]></category><category><![CDATA[gravityseries560]]></category><category><![CDATA[sousvide]]></category><category><![CDATA[commerce]]></category><category><![CDATA[barbecue]]></category><category><![CDATA[smoker]]></category><category><![CDATA[traeger]]></category><category><![CDATA[igrill]]></category><category><![CDATA[cooking]]></category><category><![CDATA[weberconnect]]></category><category><![CDATA[smokex2]]></category><category><![CDATA[thermapenmk4]]></category><category><![CDATA[barbeque]]></category><category><![CDATA[vacuumsealer]]></category><category><![CDATA[masterbuilt]]></category><category><![CDATA[grills]]></category><category><![CDATA[bbq]]></category><category><![CDATA[thermoworks]]></category><category><![CDATA[grilling]]></category><category><![CDATA[anovaprecisioncooker]]></category><category><![CDATA[smokex]]></category><category><![CDATA[weber]]></category><category><![CDATA[grill]]></category><category><![CDATA[Food&Cooking]]></category><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Billy Steele]]></category><media:content height="534" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/cf410a90-cbb8-11ec-bff9-51a75dd1471e" width="800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1300" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/cf40e380-cbb8-11ec-b73e-9ddbfa4a0cbb" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Billy Steele / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A group of outudoor grills on someone's backyard porch, along with a pizza oven, plus the Engadget Best Kitchen Tech badge on the top left corner.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Grilling gear]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nothing Phone 2 review: An offbeat alternative to boring midrange phones]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>成为一家智能手机初创公司并不容易，尤其是当你面对苹果、谷歌和三星等科技巨头时。但在去年售出<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:CNBC;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34e37b9c-8975-48da-aa39-df8bcd5badc3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=CNBC&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAf7mvqqQmpCUe3vhi-r9uRKpimsZsmqSliVdmjXIJEiJ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2022%2F12%2F05%2Fcarl-peis-nothing-plans-to-launch-smartphone-in-us-to-take-on-iphone.html" class="rapid-with-clickid">超过 500,000 部</a><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nothing-phone-1-review-transparent-smartphone-090029611.html">Phone 1</a>之后，Nothing 又推出了续作： <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3VzLm5vdGhpbmcudGVjaC9wYWdlcy9waG9uZS0yIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJjYWQwOTliNy02NDQ4LTRhYzAtYmYxMy00Y2RhMDQzZGRlNjUifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAa0Y_fK4QGyx3xT0dl3A8Kf-cG__xpcfeKBNvH2ZrlHB&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fus.nothing.tech%2Fpages%2Fphone-2" class="rapid-with-clickid">Phone 2</a> 。虽然它看起来与之前的型号相似，但感觉Nothing终于找到了自己的节奏。它不仅拥有更快的 CPU，而且摄像头也得到了改进，我们终于看到 Nothing 的更周到、更深思熟虑的 UI 愿景。甚至这款手机最独特的功能——其 Glyph 界面——也提供了增强的定制和附加功能。但也许最重要的是，Phone 2 将在美国正式上市。虽然这种复杂性的增加带来了成本的增加，但 600 美元的价格仍然非常实惠。在众多经常混在一起的 Android 手机中，以合理的价格获得一款引人注目的设备绝对是一件值得注意的事情。</p><h2>设计</h2><p>与大多数覆盖着空白玻璃的手机相比，Phone 2（有白色或新的灰色可供选择）令人惊叹。其透明的大猩猩玻璃背面显示出各种单调的组件，让您可以看到磁性充电线圈、电源线等。不过，这并不混乱。一切都搞定了，而且有一些人性化的元素，比如将一些组件排列得像大象一样。有人告诉我还有其他生物隐藏着，但我还没有发现它们。这就像你的口袋里有一个赛博朋克艺术装置。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="d3956f6920444afcb515dea0fe80719a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>当然，还有 Glyph 接口，它由许多可以脉冲、频闪和发光的 LED 灯条组成。对于这个模型，无非是将灯光数量从 5 个增加到 11 个，同时还增加了对可寻址区域的支持，从而实现渐变效果。不幸的是，仍然只有一种颜色可供选择：白色。</p><p>至于该设备的其余部分，它与 Phone 1 非常相似，包括带有扁平方形侧面的金属框架以及类似 iPhone 的电源和音量按钮布局。最大的变化是 Nothing 使用了 2.5D 玻璃，背面带有圆角边缘，其曲线使握在手中更自然，而不会陷入困境。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/1495a290-263f-11ee-8dfe-84406d7c1cad" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="得益于 OS 2.0，Nothing 最终展示了其更周到的智能手机用户界面的愿景。" data-uuid="ab179fdd-f410-3e44-8ed8-d37144d8d276"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>同时，其 6.7 英寸 OLED 显示屏提供出色的亮度（在我的测试中峰值远超过 1,000 尼特）、丰富的色彩和快速的 120Hz 刷新率。您还可以获得屏幕内指纹识别器，实现简单、安全的生物识别，既快速又准确。</p><h2>表现</h2><h2></h2><p>Phone 2 配备 Qualcomm Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 处理器、8GB 或 12GB RAM 以及高达 512GB 的存储空间。当然，它的芯片已经有一年了，但它处理游戏和编辑照片时没有一丝延迟。当与快速的 UI 动画和轻量级 Android 皮肤相结合时，Phone 2 的响应速度令人难以置信，并且比一些价格昂贵的旗舰手机更快。此外，虽然这款手机仅作为解锁型号提供，但它已被认证可以在 T-Mobile 和 AT&amp;T 网络上运行（对不起 Verizon 人员），因此在将其交给运营商时非常灵活。</p><h2>相机</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/9a59a1d0-263d-11ee-bff7-aa2c13e1e571" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="继去年的 Phone 1 取得成功之后，新型号的 Phone 2 又一无所获。" data-uuid="9eabe193-7b54-34dc-8e8b-c8f2777ee223"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>当您没有与价值数万亿美元的巨型企业同等水平的资源时，调整手机的摄像头和图像处理可能会非常困难。虽然 Phone 2 的 50MP 主摄像头和 50MP 超广角摄像头很不错，但它们仍然比 Pixel 7 低一两级。白天，Phone 2 拍摄的图像明亮、色彩丰富，成像效果良好。锐度。只有当您放大到 100% 时，您才会注意到彩色边纹和较差的动态范围等情况。在低光条件下，没有什么能跟上谷歌的夜视模式，有时在试图确定白平衡的同时保留细节时会很困难。尽管如此，与 Phone 1 相比，这是一个很大的改进，如果您不是一个狂热的摄影师，Phone 2 仍然可以使用。</p><h2>软件</h2><p>与之前的机型相比，Phone 2的软件可能有最多的改进。这一次，Nothing 不再是原生 Android 的准系统版本，而是采用了单色 UI，其中包括新的小部件、壁纸、图标包等，创造了与手机外观设计相关的独特体验。它不仅看起来很棒，您还可以将所有应用程序图标设为灰度，甚至完全删除应用程序的名称。这个想法是，通过让应用程序更难找到，你不得不更加谨慎地考虑如何以及何时使用手机。这是一个令人耳目一新的变化，不再是每次你有空的时候就条件反射地浏览社交媒体。</p><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="0d57ab99-2b92-45a1-b663-15ac01bcb51f" /><p> Nothing 还在其 Glyph 界面的设置菜单中添加了一个新选项卡，以便您可以更精细地控制所有这些 LED。功能范围从简单的功能（例如使用尾灯显示电池状态或音量）到更复杂的功能（例如Nothing 称之为“基本通知”）。这允许您设置特定的应用程序来激活手机背面的 LED。这样，您就可以将手机正面朝下放在桌子上，真正关注与您在一起的人。这对我来说很方便，因为我和我的妻子似乎是我们认识的唯一使用 Google Chat 的人，我将其设置为我的基本通知，这样我就不会错过她的消息。</p><p>虽然目前它仅限于单个应用程序，但 Nothing 甚至将其 Glyph 界面与 Uber 中的第三方应用程序集成，因此您只需查看手机背面即可看到汽车的实时到达估计。这是一个巧妙的技巧，可能有很大的潜力。 LED 不使用特殊的 API，而是简单地从您的通知中获取信息来更新灯光。这使得开发更多自定义 Glyph 集成变得更加容易，而无需与每个应用程序开发人员合作。因此，虽然第三方应用程序集成仍在开发中，但它已经有了一个有趣的开始。</p><p>最后，虽然它不像谷歌或三星那样长，但没有任何东西承诺三年的操作系统更新以及四年的定期安全补丁。</p><h2>电池寿命</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/56e8b330-263f-11ee-99b9-fa457b6fe0a4" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="Phone 2 的底部设有一个 USB-C 端口，用于数据传输和充电。不过，您也可以依靠无线充电来增加更多电量。" data-uuid="2071059e-0a16-3627-84a5-39081865c332"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>我不确定 Phone 2 的 4,700 mAh 电池和稍旧、能效较低的芯片之间的续航能力如何。但在我们的视频测试中，没有什么能在 24 小时 25 分钟的时间内击败它。这是我们近代历史上第二长的时间，仅次于<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-s23-review-a-solid-phone-thats-probably-not-worth-the-upgrade-173026346.html">三星的 Galaxy S23+</a> (25:02)。除此之外，您还可以获得 15 瓦无线充电、45 瓦有线充电和 5 瓦反向无线充电。</p><h2>包起来</h2><p>在新一代手机似乎从未像上一代手机那样令人兴奋的时代，没有什么能让 Phone 2 脱颖而出。其引人注目的设计体现了 90 年代透明塑料小玩意的一些最佳品质，例如 Gameboy 和 Nintendo 64，但以一种更加复杂的方式。与此同时，Nothing 的单色 UI 要求用户更加仔细地考虑如何使用设备，同时为他们提供 Glyph 界面等工具，可以以新颖的方式显示信息和通知。尽管它的规格并不引人注目，但它从来没有让你感觉缓慢，而且它配备了反向无线充电等方便的功能。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/a51f2160-263f-11ee-b77f-29f982531141" style="height:1200px;width:2000px;" alt="通过在 Phone 2 背面添加可寻址 LED，Nothing 可以使用其 Glyph 界面来显示充电状态或倒计时器等内容。" data-uuid="e5d22537-e5d7-366a-949d-80b26e2c0f32"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">摄影：Sam Rutherford/Engadget</div></figure><p>也就是说，600 美元的 Pixel 7 仍然更有价值。它配备了更新的芯片以及更复杂的软件包，其中包括呼叫筛选器和强大的语言检测等功能，其摄像头也独树一帜。但它的屏幕较小，电池寿命也不长。你知道吗，这完全没问题，因为 Phone 2 并不适合所有人。这款手机希望您以不同的方式思考如何使用设备，同时为您提供这样做的工具。这是一个另类的选择，对于那些想再次对手机感到兴奋的人来说，这绝对是一个有趣的主流选择。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/nothing-phone-2-review-an-offbeat-alternative-to-boring-midrange-phones-specs-price-160002218.html?src=rss ]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nothing-phone-2-review-an-offbeat-alternative-to-boring-midrange-phones-specs-price-160002218.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> cad099b7-6448-4ac0-bf13-4cda043dde65</guid><dc:creator>萨姆·卢瑟福</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 19 Jul 2023 16:00:02 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689781702</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T15:48:28+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sam Rutherford]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/ebf45430-263e-11ee-b9bd-70f7acf0f838" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/ebf45430-263e-11ee-b9bd-70f7acf0f838" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Sam Rutherford/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Nothing's LED-based Glyph interface is easily the Phone 2's most striking feature.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[The Nothing Phone 2]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Activision Blizzard lays off around 50 esports staff amid a potential Overwatch League overhaul]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-and-activision-extend-the-deadline-for-their-687-billion-merger-to-october-18th-132138900.html"><ins>微软即将收购动视暴雪的过程</ins></a>中，动视暴雪已经解雇了其电子竞技部门的约 50 名员工。该公司还正在为<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/overwatch-league/"><ins>《守望先锋联赛》</ins></a> （OWL）的一些潜在的巨大变化做准备，这可能会结束其基于城市的特许经营模式。</p><p>据<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/19/23799550/activision-blizzard-esports-layoffs-overwatch-league-owl"><em><ins>The Verge</ins></em></a>报道，员工于周二获悉裁员消息。一名现已退役的团队成员告诉该刊物，这次裁员是毫无根据的，并建议骨干人员可以结束 OWL 和战区世界系列赛的赛季。然而，他们补充说，“在我看来，他们完全没有能力在内部支持此后的任何电子竞技。”动视暴雪还于 2021 年 3 月从其电子竞技团队中<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/activision-blizzard-layoffs-live-esports-restructuring-102036452.html"><ins>解雇了</ins></a>约 50 名员工。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该公司在今天发布的收益报告中指出，上季度修改了与《守望先锋联赛》球队所有者的协议。<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://investor.activision.com/node/36226/pdf"><ins>报告称</ins></a>：“根据修订后的条款，在本赛季《守望先锋联赛》结束后，各队将就更新后的运营协议进行投票。” “如果球队不投票同意根据更新后的运营协议继续进行，则将向每个参与球队实体支付 600 万美元的终止费。”该公司补充说，OWL 的总收入占其合并净收入的比例不到百分之一。</p><p>最近有报道称，《守望先锋联赛》 <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.sportsbusinessjournal.com/Daily/Issues/2023/06/05/Esports/activision-blizzard-overwatch-league-teams.aspx#:~:text=Expansion%20teams%20that%20joined%20the,between%20%246%20and%20%247.5%20million."><ins>放弃了剩余的特许经营费</ins></a>，在因 COVID-19 大流行而推迟付款后，各支球队仍拥有 600 万至 750 万美元的费用。据说联盟中的一个席位最初要花费 2000 万美元，而据报道，对于<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-09-07-overwatch-league-canada-toronto-vancouver-paris.html"><ins>2019 年第二赛季加入的</ins></a>扩军球队来说，这一数字跃升至<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-08-29-overwatch-league-viewers-meta-goats-role-lock.html"><ins>超过 3000 万美元</ins></a>。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2020-04/1538e910-8894-11ea-b9ff-f592ebb5a088" style="height:3405px;width:5055px;" alt="宾夕法尼亚州费城 - 9 月 29 日：2019 年 9 月 29 日在宾夕法尼亚州费城富国银行中心举行的《守望先锋联赛》总决赛开始前，球迷们进入竞技场。 （亨特·马丁/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" data-uuid="bec0ae1c-4369-3894-8810-c086ad89fb77"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">亨特·马丁来自盖蒂图片社</div></figure><p>尽管 OWL 有一个良好的开端，但一段时间以来<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2022-06-09/activision-blizzard-s-overwatch-league-fails-to-fulfill-bobby-kotick-s-vision?sref=10lNAhZ9"><ins>它的处境并不稳固</ins></a>。在前两个赛季中，许多比赛<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-07-11-overwatch-league-air-abc-espn-disney-networks.html"><ins>在 ESPN 和其他网络上播出</ins></a>，赛季末的总决赛也在 ABC 上播出。在两季的OWL <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-12-12-overwatch-league-home-games-in-2019.html"><ins>几乎所有比赛都由</ins></a>电视演播室主持之后，第三季本应是OWL雄心勃勃的宏伟愿景汇聚在一起的时候， <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-07-16-overwatch-league-2020-format-blizzard-esports.html"><ins>选手们每周都会在各队所在的城市进行比赛</ins></a>。</p><p>然而，那是在 2020 年，这种形式<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-16-overwatch-league-moves-matches-due-to-coronavirus.html"><ins>只持续了几周，</ins></a>就因 COVID-19 大流行而关闭了一切。 <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-03-31-overwatch-league-online-play-covid-19-coronavirus.html"><ins>2020 年被迫改为在线形式，</ins></a>导致 OWL 战队所有者无法获得长期承诺的关键收入来源，因为他们无法从现场活动中获得收入。 2021 年，现场活动逐渐开始回归。</p><p>还有许多其他问题。当 OWL 于 2020 年<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-01-24-youtube-call-of-duty-league-overwatch-league-blizzard-google-cloud.html"><ins>从 Twitch 转移到 YouTube</ins></a>时，收视率大幅下降。尽管过去几年<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/krisholt/2021/09/03/overwatch-league-regular-season-viewership-2021-youtube/?sh=37cf6af9e534"><ins>收视率出现了一些显着的峰值</ins></a>，但联盟似乎仍然<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://esi.si.com/overwatch/is-the-overwatch-league-in-trouble-viewership-has-fans-worried"><ins>难以</ins></a>吸引眼球。 <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/krisholt/2021/08/05/coca-cola-and-state-farm-are-re-evaluating-their-overwatch-league-partnerships/?sh=3f3b257f5448"><ins>可口可乐</ins></a>、 <a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.polygon.com/22607861/activision-blizzard-t-mobile-overwatch-league-call-of-duty-cod-league-esports"><ins>T-Mobile</ins></a>和家乐氏等赞助商在 2021 年<a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/california-sues-activision-blizzard-090352763.html">发起诉讼</a>后逃离了这艘船，其中包括指控动视暴雪普遍存在性骚扰和歧视。</p><p>过去几年，中国一直是《猫头鹰》收视率最高的市场之一。然而， <a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/overwatch-2/"><em><ins>《守望先锋 2》</ins></em></a> <em>&nbsp;</em>在与在那里发行游戏的网易的合作关系<a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/blizzard-games-like-world-of-warcraft-will-go-offline-in-china-next-year-084952778.html"><ins>结束</ins></a>后，大多数其他暴雪游戏目前都无法在该国上市。这可能会影响整个国家对《守望先锋》生态系统的兴趣。 （动视暴雪在财报中指出，今年第二季度“ <em>《守望先锋 2》</em>的参与度和玩家投资连续下降”，但希望下个月的<a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/overwatch-2s-story-missions-and-new-pvp-mode-will-land-on-august-10th-191905129.html"><ins>软重启和重大更新</ins></a>能够让玩家回归。）</p><p>今年，暴雪试图为《守望先锋联赛》带来更多乐趣，为来自第二级《挑战者系列赛》的队伍开辟了一条途径，让他们首次参加《守望先锋》最高级别的电子竞技比赛。六月，在上半赛季未能派出球队后，成都猎人队成为第一支永远<a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://www.ggrecon.com/articles/chengdu-hunters-exit-overwatch-league/"><ins>离开《守望先锋联赛》的</ins></a>球队。</p><p> OWL球队老板长期以来一直声称他们没有从联盟中赚到足够的钱。今年早些时候，电子竞技记者 Jacob Wolf <a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://www.jacobwolf.report/p/overwatch-league-teams-start-collective"><ins>报道称</ins></a>，OWL 团队聘请了一家律师事务所与动视暴雪进行谈判，以寻求某种经济救济，“在多年的高运营成本和不断未能兑现收入承诺之后”。 <em>Sports Business Journal</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.sportsbusinessjournal.com/SB-Blogs/Newsletter-Esports/2023/01/19.aspx"><ins>noted</ins></a> that teams receive around $1 million from OWL but it costs between $3 million and $5 million a year to run a competitive team, meaning that most are running at a loss.</p><p> Given the financial implications, it would not be surprising if OWL teams vote to end their agreement with the league. While that would certainly end the Overwatch League in its current format, Activision Blizzard is still planning to support Overwatch esports.</p><p> “I want to be clear on one thing in particular, that Overwatch remains committed to a competitive ecosystem in 2024 and beyond,” OWL commissioner Sean Miller told <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/19/23799550/activision-blizzard-esports-layoffs-overwatch-league-owl"><em><ins>The Verge</ins></em></a> . “And we&#39;re building toward a revitalized global scene that prioritizes players and fans.” Miller noted that Blizzard was looking at various options for the future of Overwatch esports and added he was very optimistic: &quot;We are doing all we can to make the player experience and the fan experience one that people want to return to, want to be a part of and get excited about to turn on.”</p><p> All the same, the Overwatch esports ecosystem could look very different next year. This year&#39;s Grand Finals in Toronto could be the end of OWL as we know it.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/activision-blizzard-lays-off-around-50-esports-staff-amid-a-potential-overwatch-league-overhaul-152039688.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/activision-blizzard-lays-off-around-50-esports-staff-amid-a-potential-overwatch-league-overhaul-152039688.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ca1aa229-f383-4d16-aae5-adf81310d7db</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 15:20:39 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689780039</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T15:20:47+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Sports & Recreation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="3289" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2019-08/b68ce1a0-b927-11e9-bbff-d35fe24f493c" width="4933"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3289" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-images/2019-08/b68ce1a0-b927-11e9-bbff-d35fe24f493c" width="4933"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[FILE - In this July 28, 2018, file photo, London Spitfire fan Rick Ybarra, of Plainfield, Ind., reacts after London won the second game against the Philadelphia Fusion during the Overwatch League Grand Finals competition at Barclays Center in New York. Each Overwatch League franchise will host two to five homestand weekends in 2020 as the esports league launches an unprecedented home-and-away schedule spanning three continents. The esport league revealed Tuesday, July 16, 2019, plans for each of its 20 teams to host homestand series, similar to events staged by teams this year in Dallas, Atlanta and Los Angeles, as part of its 2020 regular season.(AP Photo/Mary Altaffer, File)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Esports Overwatch League 2020 Plans]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best mobile gaming controllers for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Mobile gaming is serious business now. The biggest titles out there are games like <em>Fortnite</em> and <em>Genshin Impact</em> , helped along by legions of kids getting their first smartphone. Lots of game publishers are putting out console-quality experiences on mobile, and it&#39;s taken time for gaming accessories to catch up. But they have, and now mobile gamers have a number of controller options to suit their play style. We&#39;ve sorted through the leading options to highlight the pros and cons of each controller, so you can decide which one is the best one for your needs.</p><h2> For players who prefer PlayStation-style controllers: 8BitDo Pro 2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="aa992a1d44214a31ad14c022fa3ddd02" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> 8BitDo has built itself a reputation for versatile gamepads that can work with multiple systems, from the Nintendo Switch to the Raspberry Pi. And while the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS84Qml0ZG8tQmx1ZXRvb3RoLUNvbnRyb2xsZXItU3dpdGNoLUFuZHJvaWQtUmFzcGJlcnJ5L2RwL0IwOFhZOEg5RDU_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMXE2LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4OTEyYzYzNC05NWE3LTQxNjQtYTY5MS1jZWEyYWE0ZTJkYTMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAdbQVcq9vmvHyi-nl5RIxlwmjdfb0iZux4HnTJoCy3Q8&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2F8Bitdo-Bluetooth-Controller-Switch-Android-Raspberry%2Fdp%2FB08XY8H9D5" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/8Bitdo-Bluetooth-Controller-Switch-Android-Raspberry/dp/B08XY8H9D5?" class="rapid-with-clickid">Pro 2</a> is one of our top controllers for the Switch, it&#39;s also a pretty great option for Android and iOS as well. The advantage to using these with your phone is also the free 8BitDo software that gives you extensive customization options for the buttons; it even has more options than you&#39;ll find on Nintendo&#39;s system. Of course, being a Bluetooth gamepad means it&#39;s easy enough to jump back and forth, making this a good investment for people who own multiple portable devices (like a Switch).</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> PlayStation-like design is comfortable; configuration software is robust; controller is available in multiple colors</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Not small and would be best carried around in a case</p><h2> For players who like Xbox-style controllers: SteelSeries Nimbus+ and Stratus+ </h2><p><core-commerce id="efd07758c51b455a8b25f42c4074c2a2" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> While the PlayStation&#39;s DualShock design has gained its share of devotees over the years, the Xbox gamepad is the stereotypical image of the gamepad in many people&#39;s minds (as well as the Discord logo). So it makes sense that there are a lot more mobile gaming options with that shape, and the best ones come from SteelSeries: the Nimbus+ for Apple-made devices and the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9TdGVlbFNlcmllcy1OaW1idXMtQmx1ZXRvb3RoLU1vYmlsZS1Db250cm9sbGVyL2RwL0IwOVRSR0o3WVI_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMXE2LTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiI4OTEyYzYzNC05NWE3LTQxNjQtYTY5MS1jZWEyYWE0ZTJkYTMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAStFbGl-a87IjaowshfjZj5uBLUrayG5I6ruDoZ7Bnt3&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSteelSeries-Nimbus-Bluetooth-Mobile-Controller%2Fdp%2FB09TRGJ7YR" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/SteelSeries-Nimbus-Bluetooth-Mobile-Controller/dp/B09TRGJ7YR?th=1" class="rapid-with-clickid">Stratus+</a> for Google-based devices (Android and Chromebook).</p><p> The two controllers are, for the most part, identical. They have shoulder buttons and triggers, the d-pad is the same, and they both include sturdy phone mounts for attaching your device at the top — the type that clamps in place automatically. Unlike a clamp from a more generic company, the one SteelSeries provides with both controllers won&#39;t fight you during the process of mounting your phone.</p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> More players are likely to be familiar with Xbox-style controllers; both models include sturdy clamps for clipping your phone to the controller.</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> You have to buy a different controller based on what OS you&#39;re using; the controller with the clamp attached is unwieldy</p><h2> For players who want to turn their Android phone into a Switch or Steam Deck-like device: Razer Kishi </h2><p><core-commerce id="8eaf1bcc93ed4a959508581ed785160f" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Let&#39;s be honest, the form factor is a big reason that devices like the Switch are so popular. They&#39;re comfortable to hold, well-balanced and really put the screen front and center. You don&#39;t really get that with a phone clamp or table stand. Luckily, <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfuVAkEgOYUAwWeyDCqA04dIxZ7ooWXIUjFTLjmKJtxL&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FRazer-Kishi-Controller-Android-Passthrough-Thumbsticks%2Fdp%2FB086X8DHN2" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Razer-Kishi-Controller-Android-Passthrough-Thumbsticks/dp/B086X8DHN2?" class="rapid-with-clickid">Razer&#39;s Kishi</a> is a super affordable option that&#39;s easy to slide your phone into — though the setup admittedly wasn&#39;t as quick for me as the SteelSeries options. But at least the direct connection it forms with the phone using USB-C (or Lightning if you&#39;re on an iPhone) is faster than Bluetooth.</p><p> The Kishi&#39;s biggest advantages — besides Razer&#39;s high-end build quality — are its passthrough charging, so you never need to detach it to charge your phone, and the size it folds down to when you do take it off your device. It&#39;s smaller than the SteelSeries controllers, making it ideal for throwing into a small bag.</p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Provides a direct connection to a phone instead of relying on Bluetooth; folds up compactly when not in use</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Phone with Kishi attached may feel bulky</p><h2> For players who want to turn their iPhone into a handheld console: Backbone One </h2><p><core-commerce id="8e560c6337ac45a484390299692b370f" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> The new <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAX9YBD8yhbwT4cbNzAiD3bTzYXOi0B6l2chY6XPWcvwu&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBackbone-iOS-Mobile-Gamepad-Controller-Certified%2Fdp%2FB08RL7VLKY" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Backbone-iOS-Mobile-Gamepad-Controller-Certified/dp/B08RL7VLKY?" class="rapid-with-clickid">Backbone One</a> is similar to Razer&#39;s Kishi and made specifically for Apple devices, though at a higher cost (due to being newer and from a smaller company). My colleague Mat Smith was a <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/backbone-one-ios-gamepad-review-143015385.html">big fan</a> of the One when he tried it, and in my own use it has a few advantages over the Razer device, namely a cleaner design and a more sweat-friendly matte texture. It also features Apple-specific buttons, ones that are much bigger and thus easier to hit than the ones on the Kishi.</p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Nice matte finish; specifically made for iPhone users</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Expensive; only works with iPhones</p><h2> For players who want the most portable controller possible (or the cutest): 8BitDo Zero 2 </h2><p><core-commerce id="356e91adf6ce4fc6ac57a896999c13ed" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> If you have big hands, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAa8f8-LdcCmUnOqkvZTzn_RTu2XSy7iDYlK3xIGDTI7F&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBluetooth-Gamepad-Keychain-Controller-Raspberry-Turquoise%2Fdp%2FB081HML6MP" data-demonetize-referrer="https://www.amazon.com/Bluetooth-Gamepad-Keychain-Controller-Raspberry-Turquoise/dp/B081HML6MP?" class="rapid-with-clickid">8BitDo Zero 2</a> is definitely not for you, and your hands will likely cramp if you spend too long playing with this diminutive Bluetooth controller. But for everyone else, it&#39;s definitely worth a look, if only because it&#39;s so small there&#39;s no reason to keep it on you at all times in case of an emergency. Not that we could tell you what constitutes a gaming emergency, but if one does come up you&#39;ll be glad to have this on hand. It truly is keychain-sized, so you can clip it on your backpack or slide it into a Switch carrying case with ease. And we love the bright colors, which are based on the Switch Lite design and should blend in with your spring and summertime apparel.</p><p> <strong>Pros:</strong> Cute and tiny; comes with a strap for attaching to a bag</p><p> <strong>Cons:</strong> Too small for gamers with big hands</p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-mobile-game-controllers-140023505.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-mobile-game-controllers-140023505.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8912c634-95a7-4164-a691-cea2aa4e2da3</guid><dc:creator> Kris Naudus</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 14:30:19 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689777020</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T14:30:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Naudus]]></category><media:content height="1067" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/fe053860-cbef-11ec-8efd-243819ee7e86" width="1600"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1067" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/fe053860-cbef-11ec-8efd-243819ee7e86" width="1600"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Kris Naudus / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[SteelSeries, 8BitDo, Backbone controllers]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Mobile gaming controllers]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Beats Studio Pro review: Upgraded sound makes all the difference]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> After almost six years, Beats is back with new over-ear, noise-canceling headphones. A significant update from <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2017-09-04-beats-studio3-wireless-headphones.html">the Studio 3 Wireless</a> , the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATcnHyII1ME5JhSM9w18HCn5hhojFyRVNA8sKDhuuf7s&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FBeats-Studio-Pro-Personalized-Compatibility%2Fdp%2FB0C8PR4W22%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid">new Studio Pro</a> is a familiar formula that&#39;s been <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20230719717373/en/Introducing-Beats-Studio-Pro-The-Cultural-Icon-Reengineered">reconfigured from the inside out</a> . A second-generation version of Beats&#39; own audio chip powers this new model, delivering improvements to active noise cancellation (ANC), spatial audio with dynamic head tracking and wired audio modes via USB-C connection. Small design tweaks and slightly better battery life are also on the spec sheet, while the price remains $350 for Beats&#39; flagship headphones.</p><h2>设计</h2><p>To refresh the aesthetics, Beats enlisted the help of Samuel Ross, a fashion and product designer who has worked with Hublot, Nike, Oakley and others. The result is an updated look with new colors, materials, packaging and branding. While the tweaks are subtle and the folding design remains the same overall, there are a few notable changes to point out. First, Studio Pro is available in four new colors and even the black option now has a matte finish. Where the headband hinge used to have a contrasting color for most of the variants, that&#39;s now a tone-on-tone finish and the model name has been removed. The iconic lowercase “b” logo remains on both sides, though. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="a886b161463c48eb8442dfe109d77f11" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Another key change is to the earpads. Beats and Ross opted for a seamless design here, with cushions made of a new UltraPlush memory foam, though they&#39;re still wrapped in leather. Beats is clear the clamping force from previous Beats models remains the same, unfortunately and the weight hasn&#39;t changed. Indeed, the new ear pads help to a degree, but after about an hour of use, I start to feel the pressure that&#39;s been an issue with Beats headphones for years.</p><p> Since Beats headphones first debuted, the company&#39;s models have become mainstays for gym goers and pro athletes. You won&#39;t catch warm-ups for many professional sports events without at least one person wearing Beats headphones. Still, the company hasn&#39;t issued a proper IP rating for sweat and water resistance. Beats says it&#39;s confident the Studio Pro will be just fine for workouts, but it&#39;s also clear that earpad replacements won&#39;t be available through the company. You&#39;ll need to find a third-party supplier should they get too grimey.</p><p> Physical on-board controls are back on the Studio Pro. On the outside of the left ear cup, a multi-function button in the center handles single, double and triple taps to control music and calls. A long press here will activate your voice assistant, even though the headphones support hands-free Siri on Apple devices. Above and below this center button are the volume controls, while the noise modes are toggled with a double press of the power button on the right ear cup. If you&#39;re in USB-C audio mode, two taps of that button will cycle between three EQ presets specifically designed for wired use (Signature, Entertainment and Conversation). A line of five LEDs below the power control blinks when you&#39;re in pairing mode and gives you a battery life estimate with a single press when the headphones are powered on.</p><h2> Software and features </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/289dd5b0-25a8-11ee-b33f-beeb55b5cc55" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Beats Studio Pro review" data-uuid="c2a0ff3c-ecad-3e35-aabe-1a6e3db48d42"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Beats continues its move away from Apple&#39;s audio chips with the Studio Pro. These headphones contain the company&#39;s own second-gen platform instead, but a lot of the features that Apple silicon offers are still here. Hands-free Siri, one-touch pairing, iCloud pairing, Apple Watch hand-off and Find My compatibility are all baked into iOS. Multipoint pairing and automatic switching between devices isn&#39;t available on iOS, iPad and Mac right now, but Beats says it may arrive later. There&#39;s no need to download a separate app on iOS to access the settings though, they&#39;re also available in the Control Center. For Android users, the Beats app offers one-touch pairing via Google Fast Pair, automatic connection to Android or Chrome devices through your Google account, seamless device transitions, Find My Device, customization and widgets.</p><p> Beats has added Transparency Mode to the Studio Pro, giving its over-ear headphones a very useful tool that was missing from the Studio 3. The company&#39;s audio chip also powers Spatial Audio with dynamic head tracking. While the previous model supported immersive sound, it didn&#39;t offer head tracking or the ability to personalize audio, the latter of which Apple debuted last year.</p><p> For the first time, Beats has enabled USB-C wired audio on the Studio Pro. In addition to listening to high-resolution and lossless tunes, you can also take calls while the headphones are actively charging. The Studio Pro has a built-in digital-to-analog converter (DAC) that can accommodate sample rates up to 24-bit/48kHz. That&#39;s enough to handle the high-res streaming from Apple Music, Amazon Music HD and Tidal. Beats has also included three USB-C sounds profiles for wired listening: Signature, Entertainment and Conversation. As the names suggest, each one is tailored to music, movies/TV shows and calls, adjusting the frequency curve for what the company thinks is the best in each scenario. And yes, there&#39;s still 3.5mm playback, which can be used with ANC and Transparency Mode as needed.</p><h2> Sound quality </h2><p></p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/289ceb50-25a8-11ee-bb63-cd3eb3ed509d" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Beats Studio Pro review" data-uuid="a6ae57f4-9b01-3ba5-b2da-dac76c82b7c2"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Inside, Beats swapped out the drivers for new 40mm units. A two-layer diaphragm combines with micro vents and fine acoustic mesh to streamline the airflow and minimize distortion. The company says the new drivers can provide “near-zero” distortion even at high volumes, which is an up to 80 percent improvement from the Studio 3. That claim holds true as the Studio Pro doesn&#39;t distort when you crank it up to the eye-watering full volume. However, what the new components have done to improve clarity while providing a more balanced sound profile is more impressive.</p><p> In its early days, Beats had a reputation for being too heavy-handed with the bass. While that hasn&#39;t been the case for a while, the company still has a propensity to highlight low-end. For the Studio Pro, there&#39;s still ample bass when a track calls for it, but that boom doesn&#39;t come at the sacrifice of mids and highs – or more importantly detail. Even the driving thump of the kick drum on TesseracT&#39;s “War of Being” has noticeable texture throughout the song. It&#39;s not just a repetitive boom.</p><p> Overall, the attention to clarity and the even-handed tuning across the EQ curve gives the Studio Pro quite immersive sound out of the box. Everything seems open and airy, with even the instruments in chaotic metal tracks remaining perfectly discernible. Turn on something softer like Charles Wesley Godwin&#39;s <em>Live From The Church</em> or Nickel Creek&#39;s <em>Celebrants</em> (country and bluegrass, respectively), and you immediately hear the layers of acoustic instruments and finer detail unique to each. Those records can sound like you&#39;re in the room while they&#39;re being recorded on the best-sounding headphones, and there&#39;s a sense of that on the Studio Pro. As you might expect, this latest Beats model excels with hip-hop tracks. The droning bass lines on albums like Killer Mike&#39;s <em>MICHAEL</em> lay a thick foundation for the rest of the song to be built.</p><p> While Spatial Audio returns, chances are it won&#39;t sway your buying decision. The integration is similar to previous Beats and Apple earbuds and headphones, with Personalized Spatial Audio added in this time around. The technology still simulates the sound of 64 speakers, capable of moving with you if you have head tracking enabled. If you&#39;ve experienced Spatial Audio before, you know exactly what to expect: slightly louder, more airy tunes where the technology&#39;s immersive nature can vary from album to album and genre to genre. When it hits though, like on Pearl Jam&#39;s “Even Flow,” older tracks have new life. With boygenius&#39; <em>The Record</em> though, I can&#39;t tell the difference when Spatial Audio is on. I&#39;m also less sold on the dynamic head tracking Beats added on the Studio Pro. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/289d1260-25a8-11ee-9fd7-e6929aa9ec87" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Beats Studio Pro review" data-uuid="f09e13e9-6e3d-337e-93f2-85f48650d08a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Then there are the new USB-C EQ profiles. When you&#39;re connected to a computer or other compatible device, ANC and Transparency mode are disabled. Instead, the power button on the Studio Pro cycles through wired presets for music, entertainment and calls. That 5-LED array below the power control indicates which profile you&#39;re on and will be essential until you memorize the audible tones for each one. Signature and Conversation work best for music and calls respectively, while I&#39;m less impressed by the Entertainment setting. All three are fine, but those two are the ones I found myself coming back to in wired mode. Like Spatial Audio content in Dolby Atmos, mileage can vary listening to lossless tunes via Apple Music. Some albums are noticeably better with wired USB-C, while others sound nearly identical to streaming over Bluetooth.</p><p> Although Beats doesn&#39;t quantify with a number, it says ANC performance is improved on the Studio Pro when compared to the Studio 3. Fully adaptive active noise cancellation uses outward facing mics to monitor your environment while inward pointing units catch any sounds that might sneak through due to fit. The company explains that the ANC boost is also partially due to updated microphones all around as they have higher sensitivity and a better signal-to-noise ratio. While the Studio Pro doesn&#39;t beat the noise-blocking powers of Bose or Sony, the ANC on the Studio Pro is noticeably better than the Studio 3 – especially for things like television noise and human voices. And similar to the previous model, the latest Beats headphones analyze audio up to 48,000 times per second to maintain pristine clarity.</p><p> Lastly, let&#39;s discuss Transparency Mode. While I welcome the inclusion here over not offering ambient sound at all, I did have higher hopes. It works fine, but lacks the natural clarity of Apple&#39;s AirPods Max or AirPods Pro. I thought Beats might come close since it works closely with Apple on several aspects of its products, but that&#39;s not the case. Apple remains truly unmatched when it comes to Transparency Mode. It often sounds like you&#39;re not even wearing headphones at all, mostly due to how natural your own voice sounds fed back through those devices.</p><h2> Call quality </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/289d1261-25a8-11ee-bfff-17bab451462a" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Beats Studio Pro review" data-uuid="140402b9-9eb4-3925-9840-ea18c814bb7a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Beats says you can expect up to 27 percent better voice clarity than the Studio 3 Wireless, thanks to voice-targeting microphones and a machine-learning algorithm. The company explains that it trained the system on over 7,000 hours of “real-world environments” in order to create a setup that can “precisely hone in” on your voice. Those are lofty claims for sure, and part of them hold true.</p><p> The Studio Pro is great at cutting out constant background noise, like a fan or A/C unit. Neither of those came through on calls when I was sitting right underneath one or the other. It&#39;s better than the speakerphone-like quality most headphones and earbuds offer, but it isn&#39;t pristine.</p><h2>电池寿命</h2><p>When it comes to battery life, Beats says you can expect up to 40 hours with ANC off. That&#39;s the same figure it promised on the Studio 3. However, with noise cancellation or Transparency Mode enabled, the company offers two hours more than the previous model at 24 hours. There&#39;s still a quick-charge feature here, dubbed Fast Fuel, that gives you up to four hours of use in just 10 minutes.</p><p> During my tests with the Studio Pro, I still had 23 percent battery left after 25 hours of use with either ANC or ambient sound active. That&#39;s also doing a mix of music, podcasts, streaming TV and taking calls. I powered the headphones completely off several times during that span as well and I plugged them in via USB-C for a few minutes to test those modes.</p><h2> The competition </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/289e4ae0-25a8-11ee-9f7a-3d8f68c11a76" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Beats Studio Pro review" data-uuid="ec76c484-ab00-35cf-9ddc-94fb3c34efe8"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> When it comes to flagship headphones at this price, Beats&#39; biggest competition remains Sony and Bose. Sony&#39;s 1000X line has been our top pick for <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-headphones-150030794.html">best wireless headphones</a> for years, as the company&#39;s mix of stellar sound, powerful noise cancellation and a literal truckload of handy features is unmatched. With the latest version, <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-wh-1000xm5-review-160045478.html">the $400 WH-1000XM5</a> , the company simply packs so much into their headphones that many others can&#39;t compete. <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-08-16-bose-700-headphones-review.html">The Bose 700</a> is that company&#39;s best option, which is currently available for about $10 less than Sony&#39;s 1000XM5. Bose doesn&#39;t come close to Sony in terms of features, but it does do slightly better when it comes to ANC performance. If blocking out distractions is your primary goal, the 700 is worth a look.</p><h2>包起来</h2><p>While Beats didn&#39;t completely redesign its over-ear headphones for the Studio Pro, its latest model is a significant update. The company did well to incorporate features and technology other companies have introduced over the last five years, and its relationship with Apple continues to enhance its products. The improvements to ANC and sound quality alone are good, but the fact that the company was also able to add in a wired USB-C audio, upgrades to Spatial Audio and better voice performance while keeping the price the same is notable. There&#39;s no doubt these are still premium headphones, but the Studio Pro positions Beats to better compete with the likes of Sony and Bose in a number of areas where it used to fall short.</p><p> Beats Studio Pro is available to order today in black, brown, navy and Sandstone color options for $350. The headphones will be available at Apple retail stores and other resellers starting tomorrow, July 20th.</p><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="0383ed78-b0f2-42c0-8b52-43838bef6851" /><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/beats-studio-pro-review-upgraded-sound-makes-all-the-difference-140058369.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/beats-studio-pro-review-upgraded-sound-makes-all-the-difference-140058369.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> dca66923-fbcd-4caa-bc09-4ec902e843dd</guid><dc:creator> Billy Steele</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 19 Jul 2023 14:00:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689779061</ingested><modified> 2023-07-19T15:04:29+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Speakers & Headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Billy Steele]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/289ec010-25a8-11ee-9fdf-417abb886719" width="2000"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="http